<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-615-899  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 615 899.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  Nov 19 1990 v7 n47 p25(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>MCI donates E-mail boxes, usage fees to ITU members.andO;(International Telecommunications Union)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Molloy, Maureen.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>MCI Communications Corp is donating electronic mail services to3,000 International Telecommunications Union (ITU) members to helpthe United Nations organization in its promotion of standards andfree and open communications throughout the world.andP;  ITU plans andregulates worldwide telecommunications systems and includes theConsultative Committee on International Telephony and Telegraphyand the International Radio Consultative Committee.andP;  MCI'sdonation includes up to 3,000 MCI Mail mailboxes and a maximum of$1,000,000 in usage.andP;  An X.400 gateway will interconnect MCI'sMail service with ITU's Telecom Information Exchange Services(TIES), enabling TIES and MCI Mail users to send and receivemessages.andP;  MCI's donation will allow ITU to streamline its work aswell as migrate people within ITU to new ways of conductinginternal business.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   MCI Communications Corp. (Services).andO;Ticker:    MCIC.andO;Topic:     International Telecommunication UnionDonationElectronic Mail SystemsStandardsX.400 Protocol.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>